 dirt road...', '在能看得见的地方/在（所有人）视线内\n她躺在那里，过往的人都能看见她。\n一群骑车的人出现在那条土路上。'], ['VERB\nIf you view something, you look at it for a particular purpose.\nThey came back to view the house again...\nTwenty-five thousand mourners passed to view the body.', '查看;察看\n他们又回来查看了一遍房子。\n2.5万名送葬者前来瞻仰死者遗容。'], ["VERB\nIf you view a television programme, video, or film, you watch it.\nWe have viewed the video recording of the incident...\n'Elizabeth R', a TV portrait of the Queen, had record viewing figures.", '看;收看\n我们看过了该事件的录像。\n关于女王的电视专题片《伊丽莎白女王》创下了收视纪录。'], ['N-UNCOUNT\nView refers to the way in which a piece of text or graphics is displayed on a computer screen.\nTo see the current document in full-page view, click the Page Zoom Full button.', '（文本或图表在计算机屏幕上的）显示方式\n要完整显示当前文件，请按“全屏显示”按钮。\tPRHASES'], ['PHRASE\nIf you take a dim view or a poor view of someone or something, you disapprove of them or have a low opinion of them.\nThey took a dim view of local trade unionists...\nThe judge took a dim view and I spent six years in prison.', '对…评价不高;对…持否定看法\n他们对当地的工会会员们评价很低。\n法官对此并不赞成，我因此蹲了6年的监狱。'], ["PHRASE\nYou use in my view when you want to indicate that you are stating a personal opinion, which other people might not agree with.\nIn my view things won't change...\nThere is, in my view, a simple explanation...", '在我看来;按我的看法\n依我看，事情不会改变。\n在我看来，有一个简单的解释。'], ['PREP-PHRASE\nYou use in view of when you are taking into consideration facts that have just been mentioned or are just about to be mentioned.\nIn view of the fact that Hobson was not a trained economist his achievements were remarkable...\nIn view of this, the decision may not be easy.', '鉴于;由于;考虑到\n考虑到霍布森不是科班出身的经济学家，他可谓是成就非凡。\n考虑到这点，可能很难作出决定。'], ['PHRASE\nIf you have something in view, you are aware of it and your actions are aimed towards it.\nThey have very clear career aims in view...\nAckroyd worked out this whole plot with one objective in view.', '将…作为目标\n他们有非常明确的职业目标。\n阿克罗伊德制订出这一整套秘密计划就是为了达到一个目的。'], ['PHRASE\nIf you take the long view, you consider what is likely to happen in the future over a long period, rather than thinking only about things that are going to happen soon.\nSome investors are taking the long view...\nTaking a long view of the project, I began to think in terms of the rehearsal schedules required.', '从长远来看;作长远打算\n一些投资者是从长远角度考虑的。\n为了对这个项目作长远打算，我开始根据要求的排练计划考虑问题。'], ['PHRASE\nIf something such as a work of art is on view, it is shown in public for people to look at.\nA significant exhibition of contemporary sculpture will be on view at the Portland Gallery.', '在展出;陈列着\n一场关于当代雕塑的重要展览即将在波特兰美术馆开展。'], ['PHRASE\nIf you do something with a view to doing something else, you do it because you hope it will result in that other thing being done.\nHe has called a meeting of all parties tomorrow, with a view to forming a national reconciliation government.', '为了;以便\n为了组建一个协调各方利益的全国性联合政府，他已召集所有党派参加明天的会议。']]}]